# BROWSER-notifications.md - Dev.to Notification & Reply Patterns

## SS 1: Batch Extract Notifications

Open `https://dev.to/notifications/comments` first.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    const notifications = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div.crayons-card.notification'));
    const unreplied = notifications.filter(n => !n.innerHTML.includes('>Replied<'));
    return {
      total: notifications.length,
      count: unreplied.length,
      items: unreplied.slice(0, 5).map(notif => {
        const allLinks = Array.from(notif.querySelectorAll('a'));
        const commentLink = allLinks.find(a => a.href.includes('/comment/') && !a.href.includes('/{{handle}}/comment/'));
        return {
          username: notif.innerText.split('\\n')[0].split(' ')[0],
          commentUrl: commentLink ? commentLink.href : ''
        };
      }).filter(n => n.commentUrl)
    };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

🚨 **IMPORTANT:** Only `commentUrl` and `username` are returned. `articleUrl` is NOT needed — the comment page has all context.

