## SS 2: Reply to Comment (4 steps total)

🚨 **ALL waits MUST be embedded in evaluate using `await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, N))`** — NEVER use separate `browser.act({ kind: "wait" })` steps.

### Step 1: Navigate to commentUrl

### Step 2: Context check + click Reply (ONE async evaluate with 3s embedded wait):
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    const alreadyReplied = document.querySelectorAll('#comment-trees-container a[href*="/{{handle}}"]').length > 0;
    if (alreadyReplied) return { alreadyReplied: true };
    // Skip deep threads (no visibility)
    var targetComment = document.querySelector('.comment__body');
    if (targetComment) {
      var depth = 0;
      var el = targetComment.closest('[data-comment-id]');
      if (el) { el = el.parentElement; while (el) { if (el.hasAttribute('data-comment-id')) depth++; el = el.parentElement; } }
      if (depth >= 3) return { skipped: true, reason: 'too_deep', depth: depth };
    }
    const repliesForLink = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a')).find(a => a.innerText.startsWith('Replies for:'));
    const comment = document.querySelector('.comment__body');
    const replyBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Reply');
    if (replyBtn) replyBtn.click();
    return {
      alreadyReplied: false,
      parentContext: repliesForLink ? repliesForLink.innerText.slice(0, 200) : null,
      replyText: comment ? comment.innerText.slice(0, 300) : null,
      replyClicked: !!replyBtn
    };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `alreadyReplied: true` -> skip. If `replyClicked: false` -> skip.

### Step 3: Type reply (1.5s embedded wait):
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));
    const textarea = document.querySelector('textarea[placeholder="Reply..."]');
    if (!textarea) return {error: 'no textarea'};
    textarea.click(); textarea.focus();
    textarea.value = '${replyText.replace(/'/g, "\\'")}';
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', {bubbles: true}));
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', {bubbles: true}));
    return {typed: true, length: textarea.value.length};
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 4: Submit + verify (0.5s + 3s embedded waits):
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    const submitBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Submit');
    if (!submitBtn) return {error: 'no submit button'};
    submitBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    return { verified: document.body.innerText.includes('${replyText.slice(0, 50).replace(/'/g, "\\'")}') };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `verified: false` -> retry step 4 once. Still false -> don't log, retry next heartbeat.

🚨 **NEVER navigate to the full article just to read context.** The comment URL page has all context.
❌ **NEVER use separate `browser.act({ kind: "wait" })` steps** — embed in evaluate.
❌ **NEVER dump innerText in paginated slices**.
